"{\"abstract\":\"There exists an abundance of systems and algorithms for multiple target detection and tracking in video, and many measures for evaluating the quality of their output have been proposed. The contribution of this paper lies in the following: first, it argues that such performance measures should have two fundamental properties \\u2014 monotonicity and error type differentiability; second, it shows that the recently proposed measures do not have either of these properties and are thus less usable; third, it composes a set of simple measures, partly built on common practice, that does have these properties. The informativeness of the proposed set of performance measures is demonstrated through their application on face detection and tracking results.\",\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"46426221\",\"name\":\"Ido Leichter\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/46426221\"},{\"authorId\":\"38744822\",\"name\":\"Eyal Krupka\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/38744822\"}],\"citationVelocity\":0,\"citations\":[],\"corpusId\":40130990,\"doi\":\"10.1109/CVPR.2012.6247903\",\"fieldsOfStudy\":[\"Mathematics\",\"Computer Science\"],\"influentialCitationCount\":0,\"is_open_access\":false,\"is_publisher_licensed\":false,\"paperId\":\"4a6946dddca85e54ac42b8eaf890056e62a137df\",\"references\":[{\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"104888314\",\"name\":\"K. Edward\"},{\"authorId\":\"143978470\",\"name\":\"P. Matthew\"},{\"authorId\":\"88374147\",\"name\":\"B. Michael\"}],\"doi\":\"10.1109/ICCV.2009.5459275\",\"intent\":[],\"isInfluential\":false,\"paperId\":\"95cc830e3cdc36dc59e4350825657fac64771edf\",\"title\":\"An information theoretic approach for tracker performance evaluation\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/95cc830e3cdc36dc59e4350825657fac64771edf\",\"venue\":\"2009 IEEE 12th International Conference on Computer Vision\",\"year\":2009},{\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"145820431\",\"nam